---
import Eyebrow from '../brand/Eyebrow.astro';

const faqs = [
	{
		q: 'Can I really self-host the whole stack?',
		a: 'Yes. The entire mini-baas-infra repo is MIT licensed: Kong, GoTrue, PostgREST, Postgres, MailHog. One `docker compose up` and you are running locally; the same images deploy to any VPS.',
	},
	{
		q: 'Where does my data live?',
		a: 'Wherever you put it. The hosted tier runs in EU regions (Paris and Frankfurt). Self-hosted means your machines, your jurisdiction, your DPA — we never see the data.',
	},
	{
		q: 'How does pricing work as I grow?',
		a: 'You pay per active project, not per seat. Move from Free → Team in one click. If you outgrow Team, self-host: same code, no migration.',
	},
	{
		q: 'How do I migrate from another BaaS?',
		a: 'PostgREST means your schema is the API. Most teams import their existing dump, point Kong at it, and ship in under a day. We have migration recipes for Supabase, Firebase and Hasura.',
	},
	{
		q: 'What about security audits?',
		a: 'Auth flows ship with Turnstile, rate-limit and CSP defaults. The repo includes a published threat model, breach-response runbook, and OWASP ASVS L2 mapping in /docs/gdpr/.',
	},
];
---

<section class="section section--sunken faq" id="faq">
	<div class="section__container faq__inner">
		<header class="section__head">
			<Eyebrow>FAQ</Eyebrow>
			<h2 class="section__title">Answers, before you ask.</h2>
		</header>

		<ul class="faq__list" role="list">
			{faqs.map((item, index) => (
				<li class="faq__item" data-scroll-rise>
					<details class="faq__details" open={index === 0}>
						<summary class="faq__summary">
							<span class="faq__question">{item.q}</span>
							<span class="faq__icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
						</summary>
						<p class="faq__answer">{item.a}</p>
					</details>
				</li>
			))}
		</ul>
	</div>
</section>

<style is:global>
	.faq__inner { max-width: 820px; margin: 0 auto; }
	.faq__list {
		display: grid;
		gap: 0.6rem;
		margin: 0;
		padding: 0;
		list-style: none;
	}
	.faq__details {
		border: 1px solid var(--system-border);
		border-radius: var(--system-radius-md);
		background: var(--system-surface);
		overflow: hidden;
	}
	.faq__summary {
		display: flex;
		justify-content: space-between;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 1rem;
		padding: 1rem 1.1rem;
		cursor: pointer;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: var(--system-text-strong);
		list-style: none;
	}
	.faq__summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
	.faq__summary:focus-visible {
		outline: 3px solid var(--system-focus-ring);
		outline-offset: -3px;
	}
	.faq__question { flex: 1; }
	.faq__icon {
		display: grid;
		place-items: center;
		width: 28px;
		height: 28px;
		border: 1px solid var(--system-border);
		border-radius: 50%;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: var(--system-text-muted);
		transition: transform 200ms var(--system-ease-standard);
	}
	.faq__details[open] .faq__icon { transform: rotate(45deg); }
	.faq__answer {
		margin: 0;
		padding: 0 1.1rem 1.1rem;
		color: var(--system-text);
		line-height: 1.6;
	}
</style>
